Here’s a strong, ready-to-use prompt you can copy and use whenever you upload a webpage screenshot:


---

Prompt:

“Analyze the uploaded webpage screenshot in complete detail. Extract and describe everything visible with high precision. Your response should include:

1. Overall Structure & Layout

Page type (landing page, dashboard, article, etc.)

Layout pattern (grid, single column, multi-column, card-based, etc.)

Exact positioning of elements (header, footer, sidebar, main content, sections)

Spacing, alignment, and grouping of components



2. UI Components

Identify all elements (buttons, images, forms, menus, icons, banners, cards, etc.)

Describe their positions relative to each other

Note sizes (approximate proportions) and hierarchy



3. Text Content & Typography

Extract all visible text exactly as shown

Identify headings, subheadings, paragraphs, labels

Font styles (size, weight, capitalization, spacing)

Text alignment and formatting



4. Colors & Styling

List all colors used (backgrounds, text, buttons, borders)

Provide approximate HEX/RGB values if possible

Gradients, shadows, borders, and visual effects



5. Images & Media

Describe all images, icons, and illustrations

Placement and purpose (decorative, functional, branding)



6. Interaction & UX (Inferred)

Identify clickable elements

Guess hover effects, dropdowns, or animations if implied

Navigation flow



7. Spacing & Alignment

Margins, padding, and gaps between elements

Grid system or alignment consistency



8. Design Style

Overall design style (minimal, modern, skeuomorphic, etc.)

Visual hierarchy and emphasis



9. Reconstruction Guide

Provide a structured breakdown that could help recreate this UI in code (HTML/CSS or design tools)




Be extremely detailed and structured. Do not skip small elements. Assume the goal is to fully recreate this webpage from your description alone.”


